bio.experienceSummary:
I have +10 years of experience nannying/babysitting kids from 2m/o to +11 y/o. I'm currently looking for a full or part time nanny position & occasional babysitting.
During the last years my common responsibilities have been; Get kids ready for school, take them/pick them up from school, take them to different activities during the day and after school(playgrounds, museums, play dates) & plan activities or play at home, etc. light house work, and keep the used areas tidy. I can easily adjust myself to your needs
I describe myself as kind, patient, loving & trustworthy. I love working with kids because I get to teach them new things and be creative with them. Working with kids has always been a rewarding experience for me!

2013to2023: Babysit/Nanny, 2m/o-+10 y/o
2018to2021: School tutor, 5-12y/o
2019to2021: Work at special needs school 
2022to2023:Nanny, 4 girls 3-6y/o
2023to2023:Nanny, 2 kids 2-4 y/o
2023to2024:Nanny, 2 kids 2m/o-9 y/o

bio.experienceSummary: I'm interested in the position. I have all the experience required. I look forward to hearing back from you.

Hi there! I'm Malaysia.
Experienced and Compassionate 
Nanny/Babysitter

I am thrilled to express my sincere interest in a position.. With more than 8 years of diverse childcare experience with various age groups, I bring a wealth of expertise to the table. Currently, I am pursuing my passion as a veterinary assistant while eagerly seeking the opportunity to combine my professional journey with providing exceptional care for your precious children and pets. My unwavering commitment to creating a secure, nurturing, and interactive environment aligns seamlessly with strong values that I know are integral to a family's success.

I am available for nanny, babysitting, overnight, pet/housesitting and home organizing.

Additionally, I am available for meal prep, carpooling, driving to activities, homework assistance, light housework, organization, pharmacy pickups, returns, grocery shopping, errands.

I have countless excellent references I can provide upon request.

I'd describe my personality as energetic, bubbly, fun.

I like working with kids because of their innocence, curiosity and inquisitive nature.

I'm looking for a job that allows room for flexibility, structure and playful learning.

I started working with kids when I was a young teen, babysitting neighborhood kids. Also, I have two younger siblings.

In my spare time, I like to read, go hiking, cook, workout, watch movies.

One thing you should know about me is that I've lived and went to school in three different continents and I speak different languages.

My skills include engaging children in fun, yet educational activities, setting daily routines, learning and playing through music

description.displayText: Fatou did a good job caring for our children—she was responsible, and the kids were comfortable with her. However, there was an issue with payment. Despite the app’s standard payout process, she insisted on being paid directly through a different payment process after I had already been charged. She also called and spoke out of turn. While her childcare skills were solid, I recommend clarifying payment expectations upfront.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi, I hope all is well! My name is Alauna and I'm 26 years old. A little bit about myself, I absolutely adore children. I love to believe I have a very nurturing and fun personality. I've been around children as young as 3 months - 13 years old, since I was in elementary school. I started working in daycares and volunteering at schools in Las Vegas in 2018 and continued in the childcare field (nannying, daycares) in San Diego up until I moved to Atlanta in 2022. 
I love to cook new foods, go outdoors and simply just be apart of their growth development. Children are honestly just so fun to be around. They're so funny, honest, and just filled with so much curiosity about the world. 

In my free time I enjoy markets, festivals, riding my long board and just relaxing at home. I currently reside in   Georgia but open to travel.

Thank you for taking the time to read about me. Hope to hear from you soon, take care.

description.displayText: So lucky to have found Alauna. She was our nanny from 4 months to 1 year. She became basically part of the family. She has never been late or called out sick. She is caring, fun, and genuinely enjoys being with children. She goes above and beyond, making healthy and creative food for my son. He is always entertained, well dressed and well fed. I trust her with my child more than anyone else. She has a lot of functional experience and tips, yet knows how to collaborate and listen if you want something done a specific way. We're heartbroken to see her go, but is moving out of our service area. I could not ask for a better caregiver, she will be sorely missed. I really can't recommend her enough.

bio.experienceSummary:
I'd describe my personality as patient, responsible and careful.

I like working with kids because I am a very creative person. Hence, I love to do arts and crafts and think outside of the box to come up with fun games and activities to entertain children. Some of my favorite activities recently involve painting, drawing, and using recycled materials to create new toys. I believe it is essential from a very young age to expose and incentivize children to follow their imagination and use their imagination to solve problems and come up with solutions. This is something I would like to do with my host children from day one. Lastly, I also enjoy storytime - reading books and acting out stories, doing puzzles, playing with play dough, and doing outdoor activities like riding a bike, playing hide and seek, and going for walks.

I have always had a passion for children. I have worked in multiple daycare facilities as well as working in a private in-home daycare as well. I am a Certified Nurse's Assistant. I am CPR and First Aid certified. Because I am very personable, working with children and their families come easy to me. I am always looking for an opportunity to meet new people and I hope that I am granted the privilege to meet their families. I am now a proud mother of 3 who's children are flourishing. I look forward to the opportunity to work with you and your loved ones.

As a caretaker with three years of experience, my passion for nurturing young minds and supporting families led me to become a childcare provider. I believe that every child deserves a safe and stimulating environment to grow and learn, and I strive to create just that. My patient and calm nature, coupled with my creative and imaginative approach, allows me to connect with children on a personal level.

I prioritize open communication with parents, providing regular updates and ensuring that their preferred method of communication is respected. When it comes to enforcing household rules, I maintain a firm but gentle approach, fostering a sense of discipline and respect.

My love for outdoor activities, board games, and educational play encourages children to explore, learn, and have fun. I am comfortable caring for one child at a time and am happy to assist with tasks like cooking, light housekeeping, travel, and supervising swimming.

Hello! 

My name is Teryn. I am a qualified College graduate looking for a nanny or babysitting role in the Decatur area. I have a huge passion for children being that I'm a Teacher Assistant . I'm very creative and energetic.

description.originalText: I love Teryn because he shows that you she is committed to her job she is very respectful and have a passion for working with children and contributing to their growth and development my kids love her !!

bio.experienceSummary: My name is Chamiya, I have a deep passion for childcare & child development. With over 7 years of experience caring for children of all ages, I understand the importance of creating a safe, loving, and structured environment where kids can thrive. I take pride in fostering positive relationships with both children & parents, ensuring open communication & trust. My approach balances fun, learning, & structure encouraging creativity, independence, & emotional growth. Whether it's assisting with homework, preparing meals, organizingactivities, or maintaining a consistent routine, I am committed to providing the highest level of care and assistance. In addition, I am CPR certified. Im also comfortable with animals, light housekeeping, running errands, and helping with daily household tasks as needed. I would love the opportunity to support your family and provide your children with attentive & loving care they deserve. I look forward to connecting and becoming apart of your family!
